"Reframing AGI

Under this framework, AGI does not require a single universal model or human-like cognition. Instead, generalized intelligence emerges from the ability to:

Build and maintain internal world models
Adapt those models through experience
Preserve operational reliability while learning
Serialize and transmit both learned structure and state
Compose intelligence through distribution rather than scale
In this sense, AGI becomes an engineering problem rather than a speculative one: a question of how efficiently, reliably, and safely intelligent world models can be instantiated, evolved, and coordinated across domains.",AI,0
