"Loved the discussion. My two bits...
If 'Education' is defined as ""the teaching or training of people, especially  in schools & institutions"", then AI is a fantastic teaching aid and a co-creator and anything else we are yet to imagine. Our true friend!

 However, if it is the lifelong process of acquiring knowledge, skills, values, and habits, & preparing us  for personal growth and societal participation by developing reasoning, critical thinking, and transforming us into competent, well-rounded, and responsible members of society, capable of navigating and contributing significantly to the world around us THEN we have already been DISRUPTED. 

The term ""education"" is derived from two distinct Latin roots that represent opposing yet complementary philosophies of learning:
1. Educare: ""To Bring Up"" or ""To Nourish""
2. Educere: ""To Lead Out"" or ""To Draw Out""

AI helps in the first approach. Indian Gurukula system alone is designed for the 2nd approach. 

We can only present ourselves as  'intelligent' now, artificially. Goodluck to all of us!",AI,1
