"The interview does not address a very subtle point: if, as Demis Hassabis says, prediction in the natural sciences remains fundamentally complicated (non-linear, chaotic, irreducible to exhaustive models), then what is the point of talking about “Next”? What can this “next” refer to without falling back into a fantasy of linear progress or algorithmic omnipotence ? For the first time, the direction seems risky to me and heralds the failure of AGI. In clinical practice as in anthropology, what matters is not so much accurate anticipation as the ability to open up symbolizable scenarios, to create new mediations between the subject and reality. Models without sensitiv human culture remain dead models. School therefore remains the primary tool for speculation. The end of speculation around AI, for lack of candidates for exploration ?",AI,1
