"Engineering and mathematics are verifiable because human thinking put them in a verifiable framework. You can solve certain problems in mathematics and engineering in a probabilistic way as well, but I would not call that thinking, it is more closer to guessing and you can iterate guessing with verification to emulate thinking. I think that is what current neural networks are doing, on statistical guidelines on semantic pattern matching. I think that is very far from the models to think in the more holistic way that created this empirically verifiable frameworks.

It can be argued that we as human do iterate educated guessing with verifiability but I wager that “educated” guessing does a lot work in the sentence. It encompasses perception aggregation and refinement, values and pure logical reason that a neural network cannot reproduce yet, or offer equivalent alternatives.",AI,5
"I am still amazed that there is no talk about intelligence. We want to reproduce it artificially but do we have a definition for it? Can we objectively describe the processes of our thinking? To me it seems we are glossing over it and accepting semantic matching to be whole spectrum of intelligence. I don’t think I am satisfied with that. When I hear a replacement for a phd laureate, I hear a replacement of the books and notes of a phd laureate. Asking people to offload their thinking to neural networks is an intellectually dishonest argument. I would argue then LLMs should be accountable for the decisions they take, and by that I mean the company that owns the asset. Which means that only matching phd laureates can operate these machines as it requires matching critical thinking abilities to review the decisions they take. That proves that part of thinking is not fulfilled by the neural network yet, otherwise it should be held accountable as a decision maker. We are struggling already with keeping accountability today and that intersection is a debate I would like to see.",AI,7
