"AI can be incredibly helpful, but it relies entirely on the information it’s given. In troubleshooting, missing details or vague descriptions can easily steer it toward incorrect conclusions. Learning alongside the AI is critical. Treating it as a tutor or guide rather than a final authority helps spot errors, ask better questions and gain transferable knowledge. I like to think of AI as a very fast assistant with a lot of knowledge but no intuition, if you don’t steer it carefully, it can confidently lead you astray.",AI,0
