"For many decades, Jones has been a practitioner of ""price / moving average crossover"" trend identification

Using a two variable indicator strategy shows that forward stock market returns should be favorable.

Criteria : 
1) the ""yield spread"" ( 3 month T-bill rate versus the 10 year bond rate ) was negative / inverted, and then turned positive for 6 months ( measured on monthly basis )

2) the price of the S&P 500 resided above its 10 period monthly basis moving average ( a basic measure of market trend )

Results = forward 24 & 60 month returns were positive in every case since 1932 


6th month	price / MA 	60 mo
above 0 	      positive	return
		
Jun 1930	 Sep 1932	144%
Jul 1967	       Aug 1967	33.3%
Aug 1970	Nov 1970	27.3%
Mar 1975	 Apr1975   	53%
Jan 1982	 Oct 1982	81%
Jul 2001	      May 2003	65%
Nov 2007 	 Jul 2009	146%
Sep 2020	Oct 2020	110%
May 2025	Jun 2026	
		
	average	.                      82.5%

The yield spread was recently in ""inversion"" from December 2022 through November 2024. StartIng June 2025, the yield spread has been positive for 6 months. And the price of the S&P 500 was above its moving average May 31st. 

An inverted yield spread has typically indicated restrictive bank lending environment ie weak economy. A yield spread moving back into positive territory has indicated a more expansive lending environment 

