"The 12v connector is trash, but people can take simple steps to prevent it.... DON""T USE EXTENSIONS, and for the love of god, support the frigging wire!  I routed mine around the face and side of my 5090, supporting the cable with Velcro straps. I spent most of my career working on analog control cabinets where everything is 3 phase with no neutral. When you have to plug in 270v triggers for a relay, you support the cable first, then cable manage. I applied that knowledge , and a 90% power limit to protect my gpu. Is the cable provided with my psu ugly? Yes, yes it is. Do I care? No, not as long as its working.

I have a very good FLIR brand IR camera from work. I popped the side panel of my pc, and looked at the 12v connector after playing bl4 for an hour and I only saw 60-63c.

Once again, I'm not defending this shifty connector, I'm just trying to share how an industrial service technician would address it if encountered in the field.",Tech,0
